FBIS4-35369 "drnes105dd_94013" FBIS-NES-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Al-Rujub Movements Restricted Due to Pronouncements Al-Rujub Movements Restricted Due to Pronouncements TA3105133594 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1300 GMT 31 May 94 TA3105133594 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Hebrew BFN [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin revealed today that the movements of Jibril al-Rujub, head of the PLO's security apparatus in Jericho, have been restricted and that he has been barred from leaving the city in the wake of his recent pronouncements. During a visit to the Bedouin town of Lagiya in the Negev last Friday, al-Rujub stated that the autonomy was the first phase on the road to the establishment of a Palestinian state with Jerusalem as its capital, and that the Palestinians would not cease their struggle until Jerusalem has been liberated. Al-Rujub also called for the continuation of the armed struggle from within the boundaries of the autonomy.
